	and if relevant sections of the including code bear a similar
	notice.  The symbol '(c)' may be substituted for the '©'
	symbol when necessary.

	Basically, the program is yours, but the source code and
	names are mine.  You have permission to copy components of
	the source code for any use, but only if the copyright
	statement is propagated.

	This statement supercedes previous declarations of the code
	as Public Domain; technically, I suppose that previous
	incarnations of the program are still PD, but this and future
