@node "SOX"
SOX: The Sound Exchange:

	A very good sound converter.  Converts most existing formats
	to most existing formats.  Originally for Unix, it's been
	ported to AmigaDOS, VMS, and MS-DOS; with release 6, it
	compiles readily with no changes under any of these.  If you
	really have to convert sounds, SOX is all you need.  For
	those with Internet access, Amiga SOX can be retrieved from
	amiga.physik.unizh.ch (and AmiNet mirrors) in the directory
	mus/edit.  Release 5 (Amiga version 2.0) is named
	"amisox20bin.lha", but release 6 will be available shortly.
@endnode

@node "SPIFF"
Searing Power Intermedium File Format (SPIFF):

	The primary format of the 41 custom formats supplied with the
	MegaMondo BigTime Sound Converter (@{" MBSC " link "MBSC"}).  Unfortunately,
	only MBSC itself has the raw power necessary to even find a
	sample in this format.	MBSC is really the only way to go,
	but if you can't stand the unparalleled, uncompromised
	ferocity of MBSC, then OmniPlay will do for most material.
@endnode
